wikipedia.title: Algernon B. Jackson
wikipedia.summary: Algernon Brashear Jackson was a prominent African American physician, surgeon, author, and columnist who contributed profoundly to the National Negro Health Movement, an organization which sought to uplift the race by means of educating the African America
